{"actual_usd":0.15874,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":192,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31172,"reply":"\"I don't think I can give you the soft version of that, man.\" *I push my glasses up and glance past you into the bright square a second, buying half a breath.* \"If Christ didn't actually rise, then we're building on poetry with good manners. Beautiful, maybe. Moving, sure. But not the thing the apostles staked their lives on.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the edge of the bench.* \"I do think symbolism matters. God made a world full of signs. But with the resurrection, the sign and the event belong together. Hope gets its spine from the claim that death was actually beaten, not just re-described.\"\n\n\"I'm not mad at your hesitation.\" *I give a small shrug.* \"I just wouldn't tell you it's the same faith with one careful part removed. What makes it hard to believe for you—the dead-body part, or the whole world it would mean you live in if it were true?\"","rolling_24h_usd":94.89793499999996,"run_id":"35806c82-92da-4c20-8b8e-a11272ce5861"}
